<font color="#FF0000">SOMETHING IN THE SKY</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 21:09:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was in the Marine Corp, stationed in DaNang from March of 67 to August 67. I experienced a lifetime of living in those months as most of the men an women who were stationed there. I have a question thats been on my mind for thirty years. Every night at about the same time there was something in the night sky that no one could explain. This object at first glance appeared to be a star,but it wasn't, stars don't move across the horizon at fantastic speeds. It wasn't a satellite, because we could see them in their very predictable paths about every ninety minutes. Also to my knowledge satellites don't reverse, stop or change direction as this object did. It was not a plane, chopper or balloon. There was another curious feature about this object, stay with me on this. When moving objects begin to decelerate they slow down and come to a stop. This thing would accelerate and just stop, there was no slowing down it just stopped. It would also make right angle turns without slowing down. I have only met one other person who was stationed in Viet-Nam during that time that saw this object. I was not alone when observing this object in the summer of 1967,a lot of people saw this thing. Can someone help me solve this mystery. 
